
extends ../templates/layout.pug

block head
  title Contribute data to the Scottish Remote Sensing Portal | Scottish Government

block variables
    - var page_name = 'contribute'

block meta
  meta(description='Submit your LiDAR data to Scotlandâ€™s Spatial Data Inventory (SSDI) for inclusion within the Scottish Remote Sensing Portal.')

block content
  main(role='main')#main.container.normal-page-container.flex-grow-1
    h1 How to contribute data
    p 
      | For Lidar data, data contributions should consist of metadata and data.
    p
      | The first step is to submit your metadata to the 
      a(href='https://www.spatialdata.gov.scot/geonetwork/srv/eng/catalog.search;jsessionid=881CC600DD9138162FE72D2F3483E4D4#/home')
        | SpatialData.gov.scot Metadata Portal
      | . The metadata can be added to the portal in various ways for example, by 
      a(href='https://scottish-sdi-metadata-portal.readthedocs.io/en/latest/UserDoc_Chap5_Create.html#import-existing-metadata')
        | importing an existing metadata
      |  XML file, 
      a(href='https://scottish-sdi-metadata-portal.readthedocs.io/en/latest/UserDoc_Chap5_Create.html#creating-metadata-from-a-template')
        | creating a new record from a template
      | , 
      a(href='https://scottish-sdi-metadata-portal.readthedocs.io/en/latest/UserDoc_Chap5_Create.html#duplicating-existing-metadata')
        | duplicating an existing record
      |  or 
      a(href='https://scottish-sdi-metadata-portal.readthedocs.io/en/latest/UserDoc_Chap5_Create.html#harvesting-metadata')
        | harvesting records 
      |  from other metadata portals. For more details about creating
      | discovery metadata and the metadata elements required or other information about SpatialData.gov.scot
      | please use their 
      a(href='https://scottish-sdi-metadata-portal.readthedocs.io/en/latest/')
        | online user guide
      |  or email 
      a(href='mailto:SSDI.Metadata@gov.scot') SSDI.Metadata@gov.scot
      | . 
    p
      | Once the metadata has been completed the data can be sent for uploading to the remote
      | sensing data portal. The data should be point cloud data (LAS format or in LAZ compressed format)
      | and/or the derived Digital Terrain Model (DTM) and Digital Surface Model (DSM) products as Cloud
      | optimized GeoTIFFs (COG) if possible or GeoTIFF. 
    p
      | Please contact 
      a(href='mailto:gi-sat@gov.scot') gi-sat@gov.scot 
      | to let them know some data is on its way, its format and size and find out where and how to send your data. 
    p
      | For contributing other types of remotely sensed data please contact 
      a(href='mailto:gi-sat@gov.scot') gi-sat@gov.scot
      | .

  include ../templates/footer

block scripts
  script(src='../bundles/contribute.ts')
